  "prompt": "Will I pass a drug test in 2 weeks as a non regular smoker?",
  "response": "Whether you'll pass a drug test in 2 weeks depends on several factors, including:\n\n1. **Substance Used**: The type of drug matters. For example, THC from cannabis can stay in your system longer than other substances.\n2. **Frequency of Use**: As a non-regular smoker (occasional or infrequent), THC is likely to clear out of your system faster compared to someone who uses it regularly.\n3. **Metabolism**: Individual metabolic rates vary, and a faster metabolism may help clear substances more quickly.\n4. **Hydration and Exercise**: Staying hydrated and engaging in exercise can potentially help speed up the elimination of drugs.\n5. **Body Fat**: THC is stored in fat cells, so individuals with higher body fat may retain THC longer.\n\nFor occasional users, THC is typically detectable in urine for about 3 to 7 days, but this can vary. If you are two weeks out and are generally healthy, it's likely that you will pass the test. However, individual factors make it difficult to give a definitive answer.\n\nIf you\u2019re concerned, you may want to consider leveraging home drug testing kits for peace of mind prior to the official test.",
